<title type="html"><![CDATA[Anyone good at pixelart? Help me finish this font from MM4!]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7187&amp;p=70350#p70350"><![CDATA[
That font looks very similar to the one in <em>Yar's Revenge</em> (original Atari 2600 version, by Howard Scott Warshaw).  The font in <em>Yar's Revenge</em> only contains enough characters for the score (0-9), the word "SELECT" and "HSWWSH", so it won't help you.  Just on observation though (especially if you were looking for the decimal digits).<br /><br />The source code, with the glyphs for the chars, is available at "romhacking.net":<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.romhacking.net/docs/495/">http://www.romhacking.net/docs/495/</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3664">clueless</a> — Mon Nov 22, 2010 3:03 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
